                     <p> 
                        <pb n="362"/> PUSEY, ARDINGTON, HARWELL, LEDCOMB, and ELSTON. Confirmation by
               <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename>, the bishop of <placeName type="diocese" role="bishop" key="place_109019">Salisbury</placeName>
                        </persName>, 
               to the <orgName key="org_109067">abbot and convent of Oseney</orgName>, of an annual pension of 4 marks from the goods 
               of the church of <placeName key="place_109446">Peseya</placeName> by the hands of the vicar for the time being, likewise 2 
               parts of the tithes of the lordship of <placeName type="manor" key="place_109029">Ardyngton</placeName>, and
               2 parts of all things titheable in the lordships of <placeName type="manor" key="place_109054">Harewell</placeName> and 
               <placeName type="manor" key="place_109058">Ledecombe</placeName>, and the tithes of 3 hides and the mill of
               <placeName key="place_109265">Elstone</placeName>. 
               Dated in the <orgName role="date" key="org_109005">monastery of Abendon</orgName>, 12 Dec., <origDate when="1432">1432</origDate>. 
               . </p>
